### Constant Naming

Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constants with descriptive names:

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Clear constant naming
const MAX_LOGIN_ATTEMPTS = 3;
const DEFAULT_SESSION_TIMEOUT = 30 * 60 * 1000; // 30 minutes
const API_BASE_URL = process.env.API_BASE_URL || "http://localhost:3000";
const SUPPORTED_FILE_TYPES = ["image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/gif"];

// ❌ Bad: Unclear constant naming
const MAX_ATTEMPTS = 3;
const TIMEOUT = 30 * 60 * 1000;
const URL = process.env.API_BASE_URL || "http://localhost:3000";
const TYPES = ["image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/gif"];
```

