### Naming Best Practices

#### Use Meaningful Names

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Names that explain the purpose
const userAuthenticationStatus = checkUserAuthentication();
const passwordValidationResult = validatePasswordStrength(password);
const sessionExpirationTime = calculateSessionExpiration();

// ❌ Bad: Names that don't explain purpose
const status = checkUserAuthentication();
const result = validatePasswordStrength(password);
const time = calculateSessionExpiration();
```

#### Avoid Abbreviations

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Full descriptive names
const userAuthenticationToken = generateAuthToken(user);
const databaseConnectionPool = createConnectionPool();
const emailValidationService = new EmailValidationService();

// ❌ Bad: Unnecessary abbreviations
const userAuthToken = generateAuthToken(user);
const dbConnPool = createConnectionPool();
const emailValSvc = new EmailValidationService();
```

#### Use Consistent Terminology

```typescript
// ✅ Good: Consistent terminology throughout
interface User {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  profile: UserProfile;
}

class UserService {
  async createUser(
    userData: CreateUserData
  ): Promise<Result<User, UserCreationError>> {
